# <%= projectName %>

Walking skeleton scaffolded by `@rgoussu.dev/keel`. Trunk-based, hexagonal,
Command/Query + Mediator, fakes-not-mocks, OpenTofu-deployed.

## Layout

```
application/<channel>/{contract,executable}   # created by `keel g executable`
domain/contract                               # ports + DTOs
domain/core/kernel                            # Action / Command / Query / Result / Error / Handler / Mediator
domain/core/<aggregate>                       # business logic
infrastructure/<port>/{<impl>,fake}           # adapters + fake module
iac/<target>/                                 # OpenTofu (repo root)
build-logic/                                  # gradle convention plugins
gradle/libs.versions.toml                     # version catalog
```

## Setup (one-time)

The skeleton does not ship the Gradle Wrapper — generate it once with a
system-installed Gradle, then commit the result:

```sh
gradle wrapper --gradle-version 8.11
git add gradle/wrapper/ gradlew gradlew.bat
```

Also set the Java package for {@code group} on the root project by
editing `build.gradle.kts` and adding:

```kotlin
allprojects { group = "<%= basePackage %>" }
```

Once the wrapper exists, the documented commands below work.

